levelName: The Bros Are Back in Town
briefDescription: The Boys Are Back in Town music level.
description: In March of 1976, the Irish hard rock band Thin Lizzy released their sixth studio album, Jailbreak. This album included the single "The Boys Are Back in Town", which went on to become Thin Lizzy's biggest US hit and won the 1976 NME Award for Best Single.                        In August of 2022, The Mario Maker Celebration Project released an announcement trailer. That trailer included throwaway line referencing Thin Lizzy. This is the level that was made because of that throwaway line.
makerDescription: DTSpies is still livin' downtown, drivin' all the old men crazy.

briefDescription: Dodge peepas that create circles and waves.
description: Wander into the warehouse to witness the weird white whirling wheels!
makerDescription: Kaito likes to create traditional levels with interesting gimmicks. Some of his levels contain looping music, mostly using background music from Kirby series.

briefDescription: Doing nice donut block jumps
description: Who would have thought that Bumpers — who have all right to be called Donut Blocks — and claws can synergize so well? This unusual duo will give you a boost to fly over obstacles and reach new areas to rise up high into the sky.
makerDescription: Although he's lost quite a lot of his passion for Mario Maker 2 — definitely having overdosed on it the first year after it's release — Tino is still a maker you can count on to contribute when it’s time for the anniversary event. A random fun fact about him (as response to a certain person's persistence that he should tell more about himself): Tino once solved a Rubik's cube in under a minute and 10 seconds.

briefDescription: Pressure plate driven on/off contraption puzzles
description: Grakowsky thought, "wouldn't it be cool to have a button contraption, like in Portal? I bet there'd be lots of applications!" Being inspired, he made one. Then, Nabuz broke it and made a better one. Thanks Nabuz!
makerDescription: Grakowsky still needs puzzles or he'll explode.

briefDescription: P Ballooning inside a cage of cannonballs moving with the autoscroll. The cage is the shape of a balloon. Avoiding obstacles.
description: Float around the kingdom in your cannonballoon.
makerDescription: Power Balloon aficionado.

briefDescription: Mushroom Trampoline with lag
description: Description is now loading... Please wait.
makerDescription: Luwuka is out of the basement once again and now happy because 7YMM is here! Wait...

briefDescription: Koopas, brick blocks, and goombas. Traditional
description: Invisible goomba sleepin' in your bed... Who you gonna call?
makerDescription: Some people think we're a pair of American scientists, but we're actually Grakowsky's grandson. He was as surprised as we were. Makes all level types, but we are not responsible for the steaming hot garbage made by our evil twin living in Japan. Kappa

briefDescription: A very beginner friendly troll level
description: Simple, introductory troll level for players that aren't familiar with the genre. Have fun!
makerDescription: I'm mostly known as the "simple trolls" creator, but you'll find a great variety of levels on my profile. While my trolls might trick and bamboozle you - my main goal is to put a smile on your face.

levelName: FIFAnts アリヘイサッカーフィーバー
briefDescription: The level of ants and ironballs
description: Ants like soccer. But they don't know the rules.
makerDescription: I have been making courses for about three years. I especially like gimmicks and beautiful art that you don't see very often elsewhere.

briefDescription: Geometry Dash like platformer where the player is stuck between two blasters in clowncars
description: Mario must prove his worth as the Jumpman.
makerDescription: Mr Sparky (or MrElectrodude) came out of his shell to make a level for this year's anniversary.

briefDescription: Precision level; exploring abandoned mining facility which leads to an ice cave
description: Explore an old mining facility that has been out of commission for decades and enter the ice cave within.
makerDescription: Precision player and maker.

briefDescription: Fishbone stealth level as a P-balloon Mario
description: Bone Bass Bandits have stolen your precious mushrooms. Sneak into their base undetected and retrieve the stolen delicacies. However, avoid eating them all on the spot as bloating might make it challenging to escape... oh, too late.
makerDescription: Mario is a platforming game? Not on Terimas' watch! He is a level maker who specializes in puzzles and all sorts of unconventional levels.

briefDescription: Complex link dungeon involving changing the central pillar's height. Red coins required.
description: Navigate a winding link dungeon by changing the height of a central pillar.
makerDescription: Having started out his SMM2 journey making troll levels, 3good has branched out to making various types of puzzles over time as well. Also, don't tell anyone, but he's actually 4good6you, he's just modest.

briefDescription: Fling yourself sky-high on the catapulting cannons within the airship…
description: Fling yourself sky-high on the catapulting cannons within the airship…
makerDescription: MakerName: Wiltini. Country/Region: Canada. LevelTypes: Gimmick/Platforming. Event: First. Height: Unspecified.

briefDescription: Music level based around SMB2 powerup
description: Let's make the best of the situation. Before I finally go insane.
makerDescription: Smpiano makes some great music. Fehwul is in charge of not letting you listen to all of it.

briefDescription: Use stars to walk safely on munchers in clouds
description: Eat a mass of incandescent gas to prevent any self harm from walking on cloud-bound munchers.
makerDescription: Pax has currently achieved C-list celebrity status in the Mario community, but this hasn't provided the satisfaction he desired. He's currently trying to slide back to X-list for the pure and wholesome reason that X marks the spot.

briefDescription: Great Adventure in the Great Palace with Looping Music!
description: What makes the desert beautiful, is that somewhere it hides treasures. #TM
makerDescription: Hello! I'm WBC. This time, I wanted to make a level by including the Master Sword. Solve Puzzles and Defeat Enemies in the Great Palace to Earn Rewards! Hope you enjoy!

briefDescription: Stacked Boos chase you and react to direction detection!
description: Welcome, new employees, to Boogie Boolevard, the hottest fitness center for boo-kind since 1988! Here in the Boolevard, we teach boos to boogie to the same direction as their Direction Jockey (DJ). Take pride in knowing that your work as a DJ is helping these boos shed pounds and avoid an early grave (for the second time). Just remember the golden rule: these boos are on a strict diet, so they're desperate to indulge. You look like a tasty morsel, so please don't feed the boos, you'll ruin all their hard work with a massive calorie infusion!
makerDescription:
Theorymon is a nerd who plays way too much Mario, competitive Pokemon, and Touhou, while also appreciating astrophysics and hiking. He loves to make players question the fundamentals of Mario with his courses in particular! Finally, he'd like to give special thanks for choo choo for vastly improving the pixel art for this course, and nickabuz and geitje for working on the mechanisms!
This course is dedicated to Theorymon's cat, Rollie, who sadly passed away this week. He loved to watch Mario.

briefDescription: Various spring contraptions repeatedly bounce thwomps off of walls
description: Thwart the throng of threatening thwomps that thunderously thwack things.
makerDescription: RadicalR is a 15 year old maker from the US of A who has loved Mario for about as long as he can remember. Despite being basically unknown in the MM2 community, he is a somewhat versatile maker who loves building all kinds of levels, particularly platformers with unique gimmicks. YMM is what initially sparked him to start improving his levels and he is honored to be participating in its successor alongside some of his favorite makers.

briefDescription: Mario is in a crumbeling ghost house and breaks trough walls and floors  with red POWs
description: This house had its prime time. But now, after years with no one living in it (except some ghosts), it's ready to bite the dust. Each step will make it crumble more and may release an unwanted chain reaction. Watch your step!
makerDescription: GreenStarC is known for his gimmick-driven style of level building, all about finding a gimmick and improving it to the next level.

briefDescription: Link course, like traditional an NES Zelda dungeon with puzzles and boss
description: For the 7th year celebration Pinktops wanted to pay homage to Chicago, his home town, but his deep dish pizza and Oprah themed troll course was rejected by the judges, he made this windy Zelda course instead.
makerDescription: Pinktops uses advanced mechanics to make memorable traditional courses that are, above all else, fun! AKA "Pink Triceratops" in the maker community, he is creative, cretaceous, and has three horns... which is 3x better than a unicorn.

briefDescription: Kicking bone buckets into brick blocks
description: bones break bricks :O
makerDescription: BigRedBoy AKA "The Large Crimson Lad" is just some guy that's really big and really really red. Also, don't make him mad 'cause he bites. Furthermore, don't feed him anything cause he'll just want more food, and if you don't give him more food he'll get mad and then start biting. In conclusion, BigRedBoy's a nice guy.

briefDescription: on off switches change skipsqueakcolors
description: Help your cute mouse friends show their true colors. PridePog
makerDescription: MangMang69 was Mang all along! D:

briefDescription: Getting over it Looping Music
description: There's no need to fear this 'Getting Over It' style level. We reduced the frustration to make way for plenty of secrets, shortcuts, and looping music from the indy cult classic CaveStory.
makerDescription: “TempestFunk was told to write a description of himself for this section, but he’s better at making levels than he is writing descriptions, so now he’s just typing things hoping that eventually he’ll successfully fill up all the required spa”

briefDescription: SMB2 fishbone/twister flight interactions
description: Fly through the air on fast-paced fishbones! Harness the power of the SMB2 mushroom to turn foe into friend!
makerDescription: Chichiri is known in the community for his troll levels, but decided to bring a piece of troll tech into the platforming world!

briefDescription: A link puzzle level using the sheild to deflect spikeballs
description: A cave-in has Link trapped in a cave filled with the ferocious spike mites. Though they may be sharp and beastly, can he use them to carve a way out?
makerDescription: Nexar is a maker who plays maker games and makes game to play

briefDescription: A level themed around spiketops/spinies in clouds and the various things you can do with them.
description: Climb your way up to the Royal Cloud Palace, maneuver your way through the Royal Guard's defenses, and engage in combat with the King of Clouds himself!
makerDescription: Zach Divine is a maker who enjoys making semi-traditional levels accompanied by custom boss fights, and he's currently working on his own super world of them!  He wishes you good luck in your quest to conqueor the Domain of the Cloud Army!

briefDescription: The Swamp is Cursed. Every Night a path appears and dissapears again
description: An old legend tells of an enchanted swamp. But even the elders aren't sure which story about it is true. Some say that there is a path open for a true hero, and that the swamp reveals its secret. Others say the swamp tests anyone who dares to enter it. Others say the swamp is cursed and anyone who enters it is said to see a path that disappears a short time later. In the end, your job is to visit the swamp and find out which story is true and fill in the gap in the history books of the ancients.
makerDescription: Silen♰Moon is a 21-year-old, non-satanic goth boy otaku from south west Germany. He enjoys playing video games like The Elder Scrolls series, The Legend of Zelda but also Splatoon 3. Silent aka Mica loves reading manga and watching anime. He also enjoys drawing and writing stories in his free time. But he also likes to walk his husky. Super Mario Maker 2 is the perfect place to unleash his creative streak. Best examples are "Double Flower Shooter" and "Who is the Composer". But he also loves to play cool and creative levels from other makers.

briefDescription: nsmbu exploration and walljumping level that has a rotating checkpoint.
description: Creaking corridors and cobwebbed corners hide a wealth of Wigglers, and a plethora of Pokeys. Toad heartily enters harrowing wormeaten hallways for an exploratory expedition through perilous puzzle-platforming pathways. Will he find secret passages filled with balloons, or plummet to his death down darkened pits?
makerDescription: Rybonez has been making levels since the drop of SMM1. He prefers to build Super Expert platformers that require more than a little bit of consideration while playing through the first time, but become more natural with each section's playthrough. Truly satisfying setups with a few "Ah-ha!" moments are really what he feels are the necessary elements of a great level...but a touch of puzzly precision also never hurts.

briefDescription: Spike balls platforming :)
description: This spiky train doesn't stop, so make sure you hitch a ride!
makerDescription: Hi! I'm Sacha, a 15 years old nerd who loves coding, making music, and creating some epic Mario Maker levels :)

briefDescription: Sequence of pen and paper style logic puzzles inspired by the witness
description: On a distant island that appears on no map a mysterious block, later called the Rosetta block, was found. On the Rosetta block there were mysterious engravings that seemed to form some sort of a cryptic code. Ancient legends say that those who can decipher the code of the block may witness its deepest secrets...
makerDescription: Rubenscube isn't really a cube, that's just his family name. He is actually a hexagonal prism.

briefDescription: A troll level collab themed around Goombas
description: If you're not playing this level, you're gonna turn into a Goomba!
makerDescription: Wilfred, Stevo, BearWare, Soupbowl, Daftlife, Bedcliff, Foggles, Major, Marble and B0X. We all make troll levels except for Bedcliff but don't worry, he's getting there.

briefDescription: Waluigi Time!
description: I dedicate this level to everyone who helped me! (Making looping music) #TM
makerDescription: I dedicate this level to all the people around the world who have helped me. Thank you very much everyone. Good luck to you always.

briefDescription: Racing along side a banzai bill while you clear its path and you're own using the cannon box and catbell powerups.
description: Dash through this dangerous castle full of blasters, banzais, cannons, and... cats? Whatever you do, don't lose your banzai buddy. He's your only ticket to escaping this deadly fortress, which may be the only proper use of the shooter level tag.
makerDescription: Hey! I'm PocketLint (or Lint, or Dr. Lint, or Sir Pocket of the Lint Trap)! I'm a traditional level maker, contest enthusiast, and hider of ninja coins. I'm also incredibly jealous of DuffyWeber's voice. No one tell him.

description: Thwomps are in tight spots, so feel free to use them to your financial advantage :))
makerDescription: Donkeymint incorporated is the leading business at the forefront of donkey production.

briefDescription: Dig clouds and descend, collecting enough coins before time runs out
description: This subterranean shaft is full of riches and heavy fog. Dig into the depths, gather loot, and reach the bottom before your spelunking time is up!
makerDescription: A maker who loves platformers and traditional levels. Samfizz strives to tell stories with fun themes and aesthetics, and appreciates a healthy dose of exploration and secrets.

briefDescription: Lava is floor, but with a twist (collab with Mang)
description: Magma mia! Luwuka and Mang decided to open their (really) hot tub to the public!
makerDescription: Luwuka now happily lives in Mang's basement.

briefDescription: Wall jumps with skipsqueak jump detector
description: Skips says he's the REAL JumpMan! He's got a new challenge for you, & NO powerups!
makerDescription: Been playing MM2 since launch, but haven't uploaded too many levels because I have been working on a Mega Man/Mario hybrid super world, which should be ready soon!

briefDescription: Ride Lakitu Clouds to avoid Grinders & Lava Bubbles in Bowser's trash compactor
description: After being dumped into Bowser's trash compactor, you must surf across the puffs of steam exhaust to avoid being minced and melted!
makerDescription: I'm a traditional level maker with a knack for aesthetics. I try to give all my levels that feeling of Nintendo authenticity. :-)

briefDescription: A crate-companion troll level
description: Boom Boom has stolen your gift for 7MMC! Take it back! (Troll)
makerDescription: "I make dumb stuff." Idk

briefDescription: short fish themed platforming level with a secret auto path
description: When troll maker kevinkong heard troll levels were allowed in the celebration this year. He imediatly started working on a platforming level?!? However the fish could still stay :)
makerDescription: I'm kevinkong a troll maker who sometimes dabbled into short gimicky platforming levels. Also hi :)

briefDescription: Multiplayer Puzzle using screen scroll lock
description: Four friends entered this winter wonderland only to become separated. They can see one another, but a mysterious force will not allow them to join together. Players must figure out the puzzle on their own screen while sharing items and resources in order to escape the Crossroads. 4 players are required. Voice chat is highly recommended to coordinate.
makerDescription: I'm the RenaldoMun. I love to connect people for fun and laughs. Multiplayer levels have become my forte. Grateful for Luqueto's collaboration and inspiring ideas! Big thanks to great multiplayer crew who helped test all these levels, especially CannibalTurtle, RX7man, SaltyPeregrine, and Theorymon.

briefDescription: multiplayer puzzle using scroll stop
description: 4 player versus mode. players need to co-op through the mansion to reach the goal

briefDescription: Multiplayer 2v2 Team Troll
description: Bros Vs Toads! This 2v2 battle level begins with a co-op race. Losers will have points added. In the second half, each team will attempt to kill the other players by using player activated trolls. Each death will count a point against their team. After checking scoreboard and the winning team will get first shot at the goal. If its a tie....then you better run fast!
makerDescription: Years back, an enormous white cat appeared out of nowhere, devoured all the fish in the lake, and then ran off. He called himself Renaldo Moon. Unfortunately, Nintendo refused to give him one more letter so now he goes by RenaldoMun and makes lots of multiplayer troll levels.

briefDescription: Difficult platforming-kaizo level using Hop-Chops and Bloopers
description: Step on slippery springboards, and go boing on bouncy Bloopers in an astounding aquatic acrobatic extravaganza!
makerDescription: Lover of difficult kaizo grinds, and making levels with unique and interesting mechanics!

briefDescription: Piped piranha plant despawn hijinx. Collab with Kiavik.
description: Lektor and Kiavik can offer you bottomless salad and wings at the Gravlax Garden, the world's first Italo-Norwegian fusion restaurant!

briefDescription: Players have to avoid falling by taking off shoes repeatedly throughout the level.
Troll level based around shells, beetles and spineys.
description: A glitch free troll level to celebrate Mario Maker's 7th anniversary. Enjoy

briefDescription: Level based on bees and red POWs that has a hard autoscroll section leading into a kaizo section
description: Watch out! You've accidentally entered into the hive of the Bumblebooms, an explosive variety of the Stingby that's harder to hit. Make your way out of there with great care and speed as you bounce on them before they get the chance to detonate, and don't forget to bring your wire cutters!
makerDescription: choo_choo and FoxMaker are two jampers that both love making and playing levels, and expanding their horizons. choo_choo plays and makes mainly easy levels, with a few hard levels sprinkled in for flavor. FoxMaker, however, plays primarily grindy platform, precision, and shell levels and likes to make his levels on the harder side as well.

briefDescription: Exploration Platformer with interesting firebar patterns on tracks
Platforming level where stumps bounce in and out of lava
Use the falling enemies, items and speed accelerated spike balls to scale up the level
description: Use the spike balls, piranhas and bob-ombs to scale your way up the sections of this level
makerDescription: Has been playing Mario Maker since December 2015, and wants to give something back to the community. (Fun fact: His Mii's name is a misspelling of a rollercoaster's name)

briefDescription: Gimmick level to utilize stasis rune (on/off+twister) to freeze enemy.
description: To you who set foot in this shrine, I am Anga Wigglar. In the name of Princess Peach, I offer this trial of stasis.
makerDescription: AuraSphere tries to recreate fun gameplay from other video games. After all, Mario Maker is Turing complete, right?

briefDescription: A puzzle/escape room utilizing ghosts to convey messages on how to escape.
description: Commune with the dead to find spectral information and escape from the mansion!
makerDescription: Other than troll levels, Chichiri's favourite level genre are puzzle levels. After making a bunch of one-screen puzzles, Chichiri decided to do something a bit more in-depth.

briefDescription: navigate a tiny room and keep anything from activating a p switch, limited visibility
Break the ice as you ride the wiggler elevator
description: Things get awkward in the elevator, so you decide to break the ice :)

briefDescription: A "puzzleformer" using nerfed thwomps that you can run on top of and touch from the side
description: You must make your way through the chilling glaciers
makerDescription: The king of p-switch jumps and also a certified expert at making kaizo lite platforming levels

briefDescription: Link water puzzle/platform dungeon
description: Gimmick surrounding twisters. Progress by turning valves which opens new areas

briefDescription: Looping music level + Dry Dry Ruins from MKWii
description: TBD
makerDescription: Japanese/American level maker and speedrunner. Top 350 in Makerpoints all-time. Mostly Makes traditional levels and popular tab levels, but has some expeirence with music.

briefDescription: Autoscrolling bullet blaster traditional platforming level
description: Bowser has had enough and has decided to just squish you. Red $ = Balloons!
makerDescription: Music loving traditional/puzzle/troll/kaizo level maker

briefDescription: Jumping off of Morton's fireballs with a dry bones shell for platforming.
description: Morton is your buddy! Use his flames to progress through the level!
